trend_summary: Built-up footprint expands gradually, mostly infilling around the central highway junction and along the eastern industrial strip, while large forest blocks persist. Road network becomes more intricate and several new commercial roofs appear, yet vegetation cover rebounds on some northern hills. Overall pattern remains a mixed residential-industrial suburb with moderate growth.
notable_changes: Progressive infill of vacant lots around the central clover-leaf interchange.
Extension of industrial/warehouse roofs along the eastern corridor.
New residential clusters added on northern slopes, replacing scattered woodland.
Minor widening and realignment of arterial roads, increasing connectivity.
Visible regeneration of tree cover on upper-left hills after earlier clearing.
